  Text: |-
    Slide 13.  Custom Components 
    [Show Prefabs Types]
    
    > Custom Components (Not a prefab!) - this is not a unity concept 
    
    > Custom Components are a way to package sets of assets (scripts, models, textures, etc) for an easy reuse of them across projects.
    
    >Interface only with 1 component - commodity - contained environment - standalone dependencies 
    
    > An example of this is the Map Component - one of the cool thing is that it can be used as it is or unpack them to make use of the bundled assets in your project 
